      "message": "There is already a way to work with YAML configuration files in the project. I would recommend to reuse what is there. Take a look on the method:\n\"org.openecomp.sdc.be.csar.storage.MinIoStorageArtifactStorageManager#readMinIoStorageArtifactStorageConfig\" that reads the onboarding backend configuration file. \nThe file that is provided to the docker is created from here:\nopenecomp-be/dist/sdc-onboard-backend-docker/artifacts/chef-repo/cookbooks/sdc-onboard-backend/templates/default/configuration.yaml.erb.\nI believe you are reading the same file here, so just use the \"CommonConfigurationManager.getInstance()\" / \"org.openecomp.sdc.common.CommonConfigurationManager#getConfigValue(java.lang.String, java.lang.String, T)\" to get the value you need.",
